NG AND GROWTH PERSPECTIVE\":\"The learning and growth perspective requires the organization to ask whether it can continue to improve and create value. It focuses on investing in infrastructure, such as people, systems, and organizational procedures, to support the other three perspectives.\"", "\"PERFORMANCE MEASUREMENT AND INVESTMENT DECISIONS: IMPLEMENTING THE BALANCED SCORECARD AND RESIDUAL INCOME APPROACHES\":\"Brace Co, an electronics company specializing in home audio equipment, is exploring the balanced scorecard approach and residual income (RI) for performance measurement and investment decisions. The case involves calculating ROI and RI for two divisions and discussing the implications for decision-making and goal congruence.\"", "\"ACTIVITY BASED COSTING (ABC)\":\"Activity based costing (ABC) is a costing method that assigns overhead and indirect costs to related products and services by identifying cost drivers and allocating costs based on actual consumption.\"", "\"TRANSFER PRICE USING MACHINE HOURS\":\"Transfer price using machine hours is calculated by allocating overhead costs based on machine hours instead of labor hours. The formula involves dividing total overhead costs by total machine hours to get the overhead absorption rate, then adding this to the material and labor costs, and finally adding a 10% mark-up.\"", "\"TRANSFER PRICE USING ABC\":\"Transfer price using ABC is calculated by allocating overhead costs based on multiple cost drivers such as production runs, machine hours, purchase orders, and deliveries. The formula involves dividing each overhead cost by its respective cost driver to get the cost per driver, then adding these to the material and labor costs, and finally adding a 10% mark-up.\"", "\"EVALUATING TRANSFER PRICES AND PROFITABILITY USING COSTING METHODS\":"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}